# Beads Issue Tracking
# Auto-generated by 'bd setup cursor' - do not remove these markers
# BEGIN BEADS INTEGRATION

This project uses [Beads (bd)](https://github.com/steveyegge/beads) for issue tracking, **alongside** Cursor's built-in todo tools.

## Core Rules
- Both tools are allowed. Use the right one for the job (see "Which tool when" below).
- Use `bd create` to track work that should persist **across sessions** (multi-step features, bugs, discovered follow-ups, anything you'd want to remember next week).
- Use the built-in todo list (TodoWrite) for **within-session** scratch planning of the current task.
- Use `bd ready` to find available cross-session work at the start of a session.
- Use `bd remember "insight"` for durable project knowledge; `bd memories <keyword>` to search it.
- Use `bd dolt push` at end of session to sync with the Dolt remote (only if syncing across machines).
- Git hooks refresh exports and legacy fallbacks; Dolt remotes handle sync.

## Which tool when
- **Beads (`bd`)**: persistent, long-horizon work; dependencies between tasks; things that outlive the current chat; knowledge to carry forward.
- **Built-in todos (TodoWrite)**: ephemeral step-by-step tracking inside a single session; quick checklists that don't need to survive a context reset.
- When in doubt for anything worth remembering later, prefer `bd`.

## Quick Reference
```bash
bd prime                              # Load complete workflow context
bd ready                              # Show issues ready to work (no blockers)
bd list --status=open                 # List all open issues
bd create --title="..." --type=task  # Create new issue
bd update <id> --claim               # Claim work atomically
bd close <id>                         # Mark complete
bd dep add <issue> <depends-on>       # Add dependency (issue depends on depends-on)
bd dolt push                               # Sync with Dolt remote
```

## Workflow
1. Check for ready work: `bd ready`
2. Claim an issue atomically: `bd update <id> --claim`
3. Do the work
4. Mark complete: `bd close <id>`
5. Sync: `bd dolt push`

## Context Loading
Run `bd prime` to get complete workflow documentation in AI-optimized format (~1-2k tokens).

For detailed docs: see AGENTS.md, QUICKSTART.md, or run `bd --help`

